Under the optimized conditions, the DPV curves of proposed sensor were measured in 0.1 M PBS of 7.0 containing different concentrations of 4-NP at 36 ℃. Fig. 5
                         shows the DPV peak current increased with the increase of 4-NP concentrations. And the peak current has a good linear relationship with the 4-NP concentration in the range of 0.5–250 μM. The corresponding regression equation is Ip=(-0.1214 ± 0.0011)C4-NP+(-0.8949 ± 0.14), R2 = 0.999. The limit of detection (LOD) is 0.10 μM (N/S = 3). Compared with the linear range and detection limit of reported electrochemical sensors for 4-NP detection (shown in Table 1
                        ), the proposed sensing system shows a better analytical performance. This is mainly attributed to high catalytic activity of Pd-His-GQD-G.
